is One <em>with</em> me, and I am That One. That One is One with <em>you</em>, and You are
That One.</p>

<p>In the end, then, what seems to be <em>radical</em> to a world caught in the
spell of the small self, seemingly playing its drama out through the
field of many, many body-minds, the Truth does, indeed, become radical:</p>

<p><strong>The Truth is that all that arises and passes away is, indeed, God. There
is <em>only</em> God. There can <em>only be</em> God. And you are That.</strong></p>

<p>For in the end, even the creative teaching device of God and Son,
Creator and Created, begins to slip away, as duality becomes the One, as
