<p>God extends Creation without ceasing. You will, therefore, <em>always</em>
continue to exist as The One who creates experience. And this is why
there is only one question worth asking,</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>What do I truly want?</p>
</blockquote>

<p>For you will experience the answer to that question. And, in fact, your
experience is the answer to the question. You can lay in bed with the
flu and ask yourself the question,</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>What do I truly want? Well, this body-mind has the flu. I am
experiencing exactly what I have wanted.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>And you can embrace it and love it, and see it as perfectly innocent,
because that is the Truth of it. Having the flu is not a sign of
